<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1061204 lazyload lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/smith.jpeg" alt="" width="1280" height="959" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/smith.jpeg 960w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/smith-798x598.jpeg 798w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/smith-320x240.jpeg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/smith-640x480.jpeg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/smith-487x365.jpeg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/smith-600x449.jpeg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Nicki Minaj, Pat Benetar & Neil Giraldo, Sam Smith, The Black Keys and more will headline the iHeartRadio Music Festival 2022. The festival, which will be hosted by Ryan Seacrest, will take place at the T-Mobile Arena in Las Vegas on September 23 and 24. Meanwhile, Lavigne, Maggie Rogers, 5 Seconds of Summer, Big Time Rush, Girl in Red, Lauv, Chlöe, Willow, Chase Rice, Latto, Carly Pearce, Ryan Hurd, GAYLE, and Lauren Spencer-Smith will perform on the festival’s Daytime Stage on September 24 at AREA15, with more to be announced. The Daytime Stage will also feature fan zones and interactive experiences from iHeartRadio’s brand partners, in addition to the acts. Tom Poleman, the Chief Programming Officer for iHeart Media said “We’re thrilled to once again return to Las Vegas for a weekend full of great live music with this year’s Festival.” “What makes this festival one of a kind is that we have the best artists from every genre of music that we play on our 860 iHeart stations all on one stage. It’s a once-in-a-lifetime chance to see so many legends performing together.” John Sykes, President of Entertainment Enterprises for iHeartMedia added “this is the one music festival that celebrates the best in class in all genres of music.” “Fans love this weekend because they discover new artists and the artists leave with new fans.”